@page
@model Gauteng_Enterprise_Propeller.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="page-header bg-primary text-white py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="display-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead">How we collect, use, and protect your personal information</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
            <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body p-5">
                    <p class="text-muted">Last Updated: October 3, 2025</p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">1. Introduction</h3>
                    <p>
                        The Gauteng Enterprise Propeller (GEP) is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring
                        the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use,
                        disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website or use our services.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">2. Information We Collect</h3>
                    <h5>2.1 Personal Information</h5>
                    <p>We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us when you:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Apply for funding or support programs</li>
                        <li>Register for events or training sessions</li>
                        <li>Contact us through our website or email</li>
                        <li>Subscribe to our newsletters or communications</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>2.2 Business Information</h5>
                    <p>When applying for funding, we collect:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Business registration details</li>
                        <li>Financial statements and projections</li>
                        <li>Business plans and supporting documents</li>
                        <li>Ownership and management information</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">3. How We Use Your Information</h3>
                    <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Process funding applications and provide support services</li>
                        <li>Communicate with you about your applications and programs</li>
                        <li>Improve our services and website functionality</li>
                        <li>Comply with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
                        <li>Conduct research and analysis for policy development</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">4. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
                    <p>
                        We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share
                        your information with:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Government departments as required by law</li>
                        <li>Service providers who assist in delivering our programs</li>
                        <li>Professional advisors (legal, financial, etc.)</li>
                        <li>Law enforcement when legally required</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">5. Data Security</h3>
                    <p>
                        We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your
                        personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">6. Your Rights</h3>
                    <p>Under the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA), you have the right to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access your personal information</li>
                        <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
                        <li>Object to processing of your information</li>
                        <li>Request deletion of your information (subject to legal requirements)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">7. Cookies</h3>
                    <p>
                        Our website uses cookies to enhance your browsing experience. You can control cookie
                        preferences through your browser settings.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">8. Contact Us</h3>
                    <p>
                        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your rights,
                        please contact us:
                    </p>
                    <address>
                        <strong>Privacy Officer</strong><br>
                        Gauteng Enterprise Propeller<br>
                        Block A, Southdowns Office Park<br>
                        Irene, Centurion, 0157<br>
                        Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@gep.co.za">privacy@gep.co.za</a><br>
                        Tel: +27 (0) 11 833 5959
                    </address>

                    <h3 class="text-primary mt-4">9. Changes to This Policy</h3>
                    <p>
                        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes
                        by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
